[
    {
        "content": "<p>Does Lean support syntactic sugar for list comprehension like Haskell?<br>\nIf not, how to do list comprehension idiomatically in Lean?</p>",
        "id": 495229359,
        "sender_full_name": "Burkhardt Renz",
        "timestamp": 1737536439
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=List.map#doc\">docs#List.map</a> , <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=List.foldl#doc\">docs#List.foldl</a> , <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=List.flatten#doc\">docs#List.flatten</a> and the whole shebang</p>",
        "id": 495246691,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1737541547
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Alternatively, import <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=List.instMonad#doc\">docs#List.instMonad</a> and use <code>do</code> notation</p>",
        "id": 495247213,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1737541674
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do note that unlike python and Haskell, lean <em>does not</em> use lazy evaluation</p>",
        "id": 495247368,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1737541710
    }
]